    {
      "step_id": "76e340b5",
      "step_index": 8,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- In the **open/inactivated hERG pore**, many blockers bind in the central cavity.\n- The **protonated piperidine** can provide a **strong anchoring interaction** (electrostatic / cation\u2013\u03c0).\n- The **aromatic domains** can align with **Tyr652/Phe656** (known hot spots for \u03c0\u2013\u03c0 interactions).\n- The molecule\u2019s **overall length** (aryl\u2013CH2\u2013piperidine\u2013amide\u2013fused aryl) is consistent with spanning the cavity and engaging multiple contact points.\n- The fused aromatic system is relatively **rigid/planar**, which often helps maintain a binding-competent conformation (though it can also reduce adaptability; here there is still flexibility around the benzylic and amide bonds).",
